Mighty Beet: get an all-round topics coverage by completing level three of the home assignment:
2. Use Developer Tools to record the font used, its size, color, and background color of the following elements at Mayo Clinic:
‘Log in to Patient Account’ in the header
‘Learn more about Mayo Clinic’ button
feedback rate buttons (numbers from 1 to 5, presented within feedback form which can be called by click on Feedback button (bottom-right corner))
Language labels for language change
‘Log in to Patient Account’ in the header
Font-family:
Formula with variables:

var(--mc-typography-font-family-sans);

mc-typography-font-family-sans = mayo-sans, times, sans-serif

mayo-sans, times, sans-serif

→ Computed: mayo-sans, times, sans-serif
Font-size:
Formula with variables:

calc(var(--mc-typography-font-size-4x) / var(--mc-typography-font-size-root)* 1* 1rem);

mc-typography-font-size-4x = 16
mc-typography-font-size-root = 20

calc(16 / var(20)* 1* 1rem);

→ Computed: 16px

Font color: 

#080808

→ Computed: rgb(8, 8, 8)

Background color: 

var(--background-color)

→ Computed: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)
‘Learn more about Mayo Clinic’ button
Note: I don’t see any such button. There’s a text ‘Learn more about Mayo Clinic locations or choose a specific location’, under which there’s a button with the text ‘Explore all locations’. I’m giving values for this button.
